# Phase 9.1 — Homepage CMS Completion Sprint 1 (Statistics Section)

## Objective

The homepage architecture is now complete.

Every homepage section has been extracted into reusable Blade components while maintaining the project's architectural guardrails.

However, only a subset of homepage content is currently backed by the CMS.

This phase begins the **Homepage CMS Completion Initiative**, where each remaining hardcoded homepage section is migrated into CMS-managed content **one section at a time**.

This phase focuses **only on the Statistics section**.

Nothing else.

---

# Why This Phase Exists

After auditing the codebase against the project architecture, we confirmed that several homepage sections remain completely hardcoded.

These sections have:

- no database schema
- no models
- no admin fields
- no CMS bindings

Attempting to build the full homepage editor now would result in an editor for data that does not yet exist.

Instead, we will complete the CMS one section at a time.

This minimizes risk and maintains clean architecture.

